test_planning.dita" xtrc="metadata:1;3:332"><keywords class="- topic/keywords " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="keywords:1;3:369"/></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="conbody:1;3:437"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:1;3:459">Planning is the activity where you decide your testing strategy, e.g.,  which covered issues you want to validate, how you  validate them,  how  the resources are allocated, and when to  execute the tests. Depending on several factors, you may want to prioritize some  tests or focus on specific requirements.</p><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:2;3:794">The planning features in <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Global_reuse/Name_variables_warehouse/Common_phrases.dita" xtrc="ph:4;3:1548">Katalon TestOps</ph> allow you to create a new release, refer to: <xref href="../create-edit-release-in-TestOps/intro-create-edit-releases-testops.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="xref:1;3:1043" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Create and edit releases in TestOps</xref>. If you have enabled Jira integration, you can:<ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="ul:1;3:1115"><li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="li:1;3:1139"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:3;3:1161">Populate Jira releases. See: <xref href="../Integration_for_test_planning/Populate-Jira-releases/intro_populate_jira_releases.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="xref:2;3:1315" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Populate Jira releases</xref>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="li:2;3:1378"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:4;3:1400">Link test cases to Jira requirements. See: <xref href="../Integration_for_test_planning/link-tc-to-Jira-requirements/ka-integration-jira.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="xref:3;3:1565" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Link test cases to Jira requirements</xref>.</p></li></ul></p><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:5;3:1649">After creating a release, you can link test runs to a release. See: <xref href="../Link-test-runs-to-a-release/Link_test_runs_to_a_release.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="xref:4;3:1817" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>Link test runs to a release in Katalon TestOps</xref>. </p><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:6;3:1845">Once linked,  the  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Global_reuse/Name_variables_warehouse/Katalon_TestOps/KO_UI_name.dita" xtrc="uicontrol:2;3:1272">Planning</uicontrol> tab will show you the consolidated results for those tests. In other words, it will present the latest status of each test, independent of the number of test execution you make with them. </p><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/rizzastaana/Documents/Katalon_Test/Documents/Plan/Introduction_to_test_planning/Introduction_to_test_planning.dita" xtrc="p:7;3:2164">By then, you can see the overview of your release status, which releases are ready, which are not, along with the total number of test cases and test runs linked to that release. This gives you a presentable picture to decide the readiness of a product release.</p></conbody></concept>